      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line the tin",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line a 20×20 cm tin with baking paper, leaving an overhang on two sides. No need to grease.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{unsalted-butter}}, {{golden-syrup}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} together in a medium saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from the heat and add the broken {{digestive-biscuits}} and {{raisins}}. Stir until everything is evenly coated. Tip into the tin and press firmly into an even layer. Refrigerate for 30 minutes while you melt the chocolate.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Top with chocolate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{dark-chocolate}} in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of barely simmering water, stirring until smooth. Do not let the bowl touch the water. Pour over the set base and spread to an even layer with a palette knife.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chill and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Return to the fridge for at least 90 minutes, until the chocolate is completely set. Lift out by the paper, place on a board, and cut into 16 pieces with a sharp knife. For clean cuts, warm the blade briefly under hot water and dry it between cuts.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
